task.summary: Determined locations of enemies 1-8, mapped all skills, and determined colors to "see" live enemies and dead enemies.
bug fix for dual wield special attacks. Increased needed overcharge so attack can execute properly.
bug fix for dual wield special attacks. Increased needed overcharge so attack can execute properly.
started function for single handed specials, adjusted players to have replenished item lists, and upped the available premium number to 3

rewrote special attacks: - now looks for special attack (1-2) status instead of tracking internally - less code used to perform more logic - Single Hand style now can use 3rd special - logic friendlier to users with only two specials - removed 6 or more enemy limit for dual wield users (3rd special attacks leftover enemies more if less than 5) - code can now easily be added for other styles (2 handed etc.)

added health and mana to status, removed cooldown and added checks to see if potions are currently being used before activating a new one. altered usage of gems where items will be closed out in the event that there isn't a gem present (might be cause of items not getting used)

altered the status check state for health and mana potions. this will slow the rate in which an item is used but will raise integrity that an item is being used only after a previous item's effect has disappeared.
added heroic mana and health potion color value for chrome
